HEADWORD: Caroling
<hw>Car"ol*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A song of joy or
devotion; a singing, as of carols.</def>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such heavenly notes and <qex>carolings</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carolinian</ent>⟦br⟧
